-- Formula One Champion Vettel Wins Pole for F-1 Indian Grand Prix
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-10-27T06:30:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-26/formula-one-champion-vettel-wins-pole-for-f-1-indian-grand-prix.html
Sebastian Vettel won pole position
for today’s Indian Grand Prix, where he can claim a fourth
consecutive Formula One world championship.  Vettel, of the Red Bull team, had a qualifying time of 1
minute, 24.119 seconds at the Buddh International Circuit to
beat out Mercedes teammates Nico Rosberg and  Lewis Hamilton .  It’s the seventh pole of the season for the German, who
needs to finish fifth or better today to join Juan Manuel Fangio
and Michael Schumacher as the only drivers to win four straight
championships.  Vettel has won the past five races to open a 90-point lead
in the standings over  Fernando Alonso  of Ferrari, who qualified
eighth.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
